{
  "text": "In general, when T 2d has a Kähler form proportional to (6.9) we can apply the Kodaira Embedding Theorem, which states that [CITATION_1] : a compact complex manifold X is an algebraic variety-i.e., is embeddable in a projective space-if and only if it has a closed (1, 1)-form ω whose cohomology class [ω] is rational. [CITATION_2] In the case that X = T 2d , the variety is called an abelian variety and the cohomology class [ω] is called a polarization. The integers a i are the invariants of the polarization [CITATION_3] .",
  "correct_citation": {
